description: For sale: $469,000. This well-maintained, custom-built home offers the convenience of main level living and quality features throughout.  The efficient, open concept floor plan and gleaming hardwood floors flow from room to room with arched entryways in the formal dining area and in the great room, where a custom gas fireplace is surrounded by a striking wall of built-ins.  Large south-facing windows throughout allow loads of natural daylight to pour in, such as in the spacious kitchen that offers an abundance of cabinetry, granite counters, stainless steel appliances, and a center island, while an informal dining area lends patio door access to a balcony deck overlooking the beautiful backyard.  And off in its own private nook of the home is the master suite with a large walk-in closet and private en suite, featuring a double vanity, soaking tub, and privacy door to the tile surround shower and commode.  In addition, a second main level bedroom that could also be utilized as an office and ¾ bath are huge bonuses and perfect for accommodating guests, and the main level laundry room also acts as a mudroom off the garage entrance, providing plenty of storage.  The walkout lower level is also full of desired features with more decorative arches and another custom gas fireplace in the family room, two large bedrooms, and a massive full bath with a tile surround shower, tiled flooring, and a built-in bench; and don't miss the potential for a mother-in-law suite with the roughed-in wet bar/kitchenette and laundry.  The walkout then leads to an ideal backyard concealed with trees at the back of the lot for extra privacy.  Located in the undisturbed Highland Hills neighborhood, this pleasing home has much to offer its future proud owners.
